    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="268"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A16/99</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1928</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 11, 1929.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 692</seg>
                    <lb/>
                    <seg rendition="#left">L. of N. No. 1249</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Legation’s telegram No. 128, of
                    December 26, 3 p.m.,<note n="83" xml:id="d268fn83">Not printed.</note> I have
                    the honor to transmit herewith five copies of a communication, with its
                    enclosures, from the League of Nations, dated December 22, 1928, C. F.
                        A.–31,<note n="83" xml:id="d268fn84">Not printed.</note> in which the
                    Chairman of the Special Commission for the preparation of a draft convention on
                    the manufacture of arms and ammunition and of implements of war requests the
                    appointment of an expert to discuss the proposal submitted by the Belgian
                    delegate with regard to the drafting of Article I of the preliminary draft
                    convention. The meeting of experts will be held on March 11, 1929, at
                    Geneva.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>(For the Minister)<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pierrepont Moffat</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Secretary of Legation</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
